{"body": "Not only loading-order hell, but reloading hell. Referencing the class directly means there's a reference to it in a closure somewhere, which means when it gets reloaded in development mode you have the strong possibility of getting obscure errors due to there being two instances of the Class. If you've ever seen an error message like \"A copy of Foo has been removed from the module tree but is still active!\" you'll know what I mean.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/10827782", "created_at": "2012-11-28T23:18:31Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/8357#issuecomment-10827782", "updated_at": "2012-11-28T23:18:31Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 8357, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/jfirebaugh", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/a82409021ddf415a8027872b889c5f74?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F9db597035f77a6c1167e05ca916801fa.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/received_events", "gravatar_id": "a82409021ddf415a8027872b889c5f74", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "jfirebaugh", "type": "User", "id": 98601, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237f3e9bd3543c15100a927"}, "id": 10827782, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/8357"}
